"title": "8278: innocence, teaching on",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8278: innocence, teaching on",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A highly valued quality to be eagerly sought. The OT stresses that the innocent deserve justice rather than evil. In the NT believers are encouraged to attain innocence.</p>\n<h2>Exhortations to be innocent</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:16\">MAT 10:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:2\">PSA 32:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:19\">ROM 16:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:14-Phil2:15\">PHP 2:14–2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess3:13\">1TH 3:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:23\">1TH 5:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:14\">2PE 3:14</a></p>\n<h2>Ascribing innocence to people</h2>\n<h3>Innocence is ultimately established by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:4\">1CO 4:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:21-Col1:22\">COL 1:21–1:22</a></p>\n<h3>The need to acquit the innocent</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:32\">1KI 8:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:7\">EXO 23:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num5:29-Num5:31\">NUM 5:29–5:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:1\">DEU 25:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:15\">PRO 17:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov18:5\">PRO 18:5</a></p>\n<h3>The danger of acquitting the guilty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:15\">PRO 17:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:23-Prov24:24\">PRO 24:23–24:24</a></p>\n<h2>The rewards of innocence</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps15:1-Ps15:5\">PSA 15:1–15:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:1-Rev14:5\">REV 14:1–14:5</a></p>\n<h2>The characteristics of innocence</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:8\">PRO 21:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:14-Phil2:15\">PHP 2:14–2:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:8\">PHP 4:8</a></p>\n<h2>The shedding of innocent blood</h2>\n<h3>Its prohibition</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut19:8-Deut19:10\">DEU 19:8–19:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:3\">JER 22:3</a></p>\n<h3>The guilt associated with it</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer26:15\">JER 26:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut19:11-Deut19:13\">DEU 19:11–19:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:16\">2KI 21:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:38\">PSA 106:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:16-Prov6:17\">PRO 6:16–6:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:7\">ISA 59:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:2-Jer7:8\">JER 7:2–7:8</a></p>\n<h3>The need to purge the guilt</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:31-1Kgs2:33\">1KI 2:31–2:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:1-Deut21:9\">DEU 21:1–21:9</a></p>\n<h3>The right to be avenged</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam4:9-2Sam4:11\">2SA 4:9–4:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num35:16-Num35:28\">NUM 35:16–35:28</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of those shedding innocent blood</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:3-Matt27:4\">MAT 27:3–27:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs24:1-2Kgs24:4\">2KI 24:1–24:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:14\">JON 1:14</a></p>",
